---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Accessibility Statement | Meridian">
    <div class="legal-page">
        <h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-UK', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</p>

        <section>
            <h2>Commitment to Accessibility</h2>
            <p>Meridian is committed to making our website accessible to everyone, including people with disabilities. We are continuously working to improve the accessibility of our website to comply with web accessibility standards and best practices.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Accessibility Features</h2>
            <p>We have implemented the following accessibility features on our website:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Semantic HTML markup for proper screen reader interpretation</li>
                <li>Keyboard navigation support throughout the site</li>
                <li>High contrast color schemes for improved readability</li>
                <li>Alt text for images to describe their content</li>
                <li>Responsive design that works on devices of all sizes</li>
                <li>Skip navigation links to bypass repetitive content</li>
                <li>ARIA labels and descriptions where appropriate</li>
                <li>Form labels clearly associated with input fields</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>WCAG 2.1 Compliance</h2>
            <p>We aim to conform to Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA standards. WCAG is developed by the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) and provides guidelines for making web content more accessible to people with disabilities.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Accessibility Tools</h2>
            <p>Our website is designed to be compatible with the following assistive technologies:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Screen readers (JAWS, NVDA, VoiceOver)</li>
                <li>Voice recognition software</li>
                <li>Magnification software</li>
                <li>Keyboard-only navigation</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Browser Compatibility</h2>
            <p>Meridian is tested for accessibility with major browsers including Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge. If you experience accessibility issues with a particular browser, please let us know.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Known Issues</h2>
            <p>While we strive to maintain high accessibility standards, there may be some areas where accessibility could be improved. We are actively working to address any known issues. If you encounter an accessibility problem, please report it to us.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>How to Report Accessibility Issues</h2>
            <p>If you experience difficulties accessing any part of our website, or if you encounter any accessibility barriers, please contact us. We are committed to working with users to resolve accessibility issues within a reasonable timeframe.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>By email: [email to be filled in]</li>
                <li>By visiting: [contact page to be filled in]</li>
                <li>By phone: [phone to be filled in]</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Accessibility Resources</h2>
            <p>For more information about web accessibility, please visit:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Web Accessibility Initiative (WAI)</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/quickref/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">WCAG 2.1 Quick Reference</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.ssa.gov/accessibility/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Accessibility Resources from SSA</a></li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Continuous Improvement</h2>
            <p>Accessibility is an ongoing process. We regularly review and update our website to enhance accessibility. Your feedback helps us improve. If you have suggestions or concerns about the accessibility of this website, please reach out to us.</p>
        </section>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    .legal-page {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 3rem auto;
        padding: 2rem;
    }

    .legal-page h1 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .last-updated {
        color: #666;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .legal-page section {
        margin: 2rem 0;
    }

    .legal-page h2 {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .legal-page p {
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .legal-page ul {
        margin-left: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .legal-page li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .legal-page a {
        color: inherit;
        text-decoration: underline;
    }

    .legal-page a:hover {
        opacity: 0.7;
    }
</style>
